<keyStep id="C90046F09F76A06AFF497ACFFA0A17C8" pageId="2" pageNumber="104">
<paragraph id="724B5E559F76A06AFF497ACFFA0A17D6" blockId="2.[151,1436,1227,1542]" box="[151,1436,1227,1249]" pageId="2" pageNumber="104">
<keyLead id="C905FD609F76A06AFF497ACFFA0A17D6" box="[151,1436,1227,1249]" pageId="2" pageNumber="104">
1. Wings dark brown, speckled with large areas of yellow scales (
<figureCitation id="EACF42D09F76A06AFCE07ACFFC3A17D7" box="[830,940,1227,1249]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–18" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1337,1361]" captionTargetBox="[157,1433,184,1312]" captionTargetId="figure-26@13.[151,1436,181,1313]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 1–18. Habitus of species of Sodalia, males (left) and females (right). 1–4. S. sodalis, 1–2. Male from Santo Antônio do Tauá, Pará, Brazil (DZ 35.537), 3–4. Female from Cacaulândia, Rôndonia, Brazil (OM 21.494). 5–8. S. argyrospila, 5–6. Male from Antonina, Paraná, Brazil (OM 14.223), 7–8. Female from Pontal do Paraná, Paraná, Brazil (OM 25.358). 9–12. S. coler, 9–10. Male from Pontal do Paraná, Paraná, Brazil (DZ 35.842), 11–12. Female from Seara, Santa Catarina, Brazil (DZ 35.696). 13–16. S. petiti sp. nov., 13–14. Male holotype from Alluriquin, Ecuador (OM 52.619). 15–16. Female allotype from Alluriguin, Ecuador (DZ 31.487). 17–18. S. spangla comb. nov., male from Oso Perdido, Amazonas, Peru (OM 83.945). Scale bar: 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423891" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4423891/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="104">Figs 13–18</figureCitation>
)....................................... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="724B5E559F76A06AFF497AEDFA0A17C8" blockId="2.[151,1436,1227,1542]" box="[151,1436,1256,1279]" pageId="2" pageNumber="104">
<keyLead id="C905FD609F76A06AFF497AEDFA0A17C8" box="[151,1436,1256,1279]" pageId="2" pageNumber="104">
- Wings mostly dark brown, almost without yellow scales (
<figureCitation id="EACF42D09F76A06AFCD47AECFCFC17C9" box="[778,874,1256,1279]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–18" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1337,1361]" captionTargetBox="[157,1433,184,1312]" captionTargetId="figure-26@13.[151,1436,181,1313]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 1–18. Habitus of species of Sodalia, males (left) and females (right). 1–4. S. sodalis, 1–2. Male from Santo Antônio do Tauá, Pará, Brazil (DZ 35.537), 3–4. Female from Cacaulândia, Rôndonia, Brazil (OM 21.494). 5–8. S. argyrospila, 5–6. Male from Antonina, Paraná, Brazil (OM 14.223), 7–8. Female from Pontal do Paraná, Paraná, Brazil (OM 25.358). 9–12. S. coler, 9–10. Male from Pontal do Paraná, Paraná, Brazil (DZ 35.842), 11–12. Female from Seara, Santa Catarina, Brazil (DZ 35.696). 13–16. S. petiti sp. nov., 13–14. Male holotype from Alluriquin, Ecuador (OM 52.619). 15–16. Female allotype from Alluriguin, Ecuador (DZ 31.487). 17–18. S. spangla comb. nov., male from Oso Perdido, Amazonas, Peru (OM 83.945). Scale bar: 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423891" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4423891/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="104">Figs 1–12</figureCitation>
)............................................. 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="C90046F09F76A06AFF497B02FA0A1645" pageId="2" pageNumber="104">
<paragraph id="724B5E559F76A06AFF497B02FA0A160E" blockId="2.[151,1436,1227,1542]" pageId="2" pageNumber="104">
<keyLead id="C905FD609F76A06AFF497B02FA0A160E" pageId="2" pageNumber="104">
2. Head and thorax dorsally covered with green scales (
<figureCitation id="EACF42D09F76A06AFD017B02FCB1162A" box="[735,807,1286,1308]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–28" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,1327,1871]" captionTargetId="figure-224@14.[151,1436,1321,1874]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 24–28. Head and thorax of species of Sodalia in dorsal view. 24. S. sodalis, male from Yavita, Amazonas, Venezuela (OM 39.809). 25. S. argyrospila, male from Joinville, Santa Catarina, Brazil (DZ 35.654). 26. S. coler, male from Pontal do Paraná, Paraná, Brazil (DZ 35.842). 27. S. petiti sp. nov., male holotype. 28. S. spangla comb. nov., male from Oso Perdido, Amazonas, Peru (OM 83.945). Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423895" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4423895/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="104">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
); forewing apex rounded; DFW and DHW with yellow speckling restricted to submarginal areas (
<figureCitation id="EACF42D09F76A06AFDCA7B27FD14160F" box="[532,642,1315,1337]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–18" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1337,1361]" captionTargetBox="[157,1433,184,1312]" captionTargetId="figure-26@13.[151,1436,181,1313]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 1–18. Habitus of species of Sodalia, males (left) and females (right). 1–4. S. sodalis, 1–2. Male from Santo Antônio do Tauá, Pará, Brazil (DZ 35.537), 3–4. Female from Cacaulândia, Rôndonia, Brazil (OM 21.494). 5–8. S. argyrospila, 5–6. Male from Antonina, Paraná, Brazil (OM 14.223), 7–8. Female from Pontal do Paraná, Paraná, Brazil (OM 25.358). 9–12. S. coler, 9–10. Male from Pontal do Paraná, Paraná, Brazil (DZ 35.842), 11–12. Female from Seara, Santa Catarina, Brazil (DZ 35.696). 13–16. S. petiti sp. nov., 13–14. Male holotype from Alluriquin, Ecuador (OM 52.619). 15–16. Female allotype from Alluriguin, Ecuador (DZ 31.487). 17–18. S. spangla comb. nov., male from Oso Perdido, Amazonas, Peru (OM 83.945). Scale bar: 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423891" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4423891/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="104">Figs 13–16</figureCitation>
).................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="B5F425D69F76A06AFADE7B27FADF160F" authority="Gaviria-Ortiz &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Carneiro &amp; Warren &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande, 2020" authorityName="Gaviria-Ortiz &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Carneiro &amp; Warren &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande" authorityYear="2020" box="[1280,1353,1315,1337]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Sodalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petiti" status="sp. nov.">
